{"id":1055,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Donanım","icon":"🔁","word":"Hub","syl":["Hub"],"ph":"/hʌb/","wt":"noun","tr":"Ağ Dağıtıcısı","tpl":"The ___ connects multiple computers.","sent":"The <strong>hub</strong> connects multiple computers on the local network.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Switch","Router","LAN"],"why":"Hub vs Switch is a classic networking exam question.","da":"What is the difference between a hub and switch?","db":"A hub sends to all, a switch only sends to the right device."},
{"id":1056,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Donanım","icon":"🔀","word":"Switch","syl":["Switch"],"ph":"/swɪtʃ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Ağ Anahtarı","tpl":"A ___ is smarter than a hub.","sent":"A <strong>switch</strong> is smarter than a hub because it targets data correctly.","str":"S+V+Adj","rel":["Hub","Router","VLAN"],"why":"Network switch is core networking vocabulary.","da":"The network is very slow.","db":"Maybe the switch needs restarting."},
{"id":1057,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔧","word":"Debug","syl":["De","bug"],"ph":"/diːˈbʌɡ/","wt":"verb","tr":"Hata Ayıklamak","tpl":"I need to ___ this code.","sent":"I need to <strong>debug</strong> this code before the deadline.","str":"Modal+V+O","rel":["Bug","Fix","Breakpoint"],"why":"Debugging is 50% of every developer's job.","da":"The function gives wrong output.","db":"Let me debug it step by step."},
{"id":1058,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📦","word":"Library","syl":["Li","brar","y"],"ph":"/ˈlaɪbreri/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kütüphane","tpl":"Import the ___ at the top.","sent":"Import the <strong>library</strong> at the top of your file.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Framework","Package","Import"],"why":"Libraries save hours of work — used in every project.","da":"Do I have to write all this from scratch?","db":"No, just use the pandas library."},
{"id":1059,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🏗️","word":"Framework","syl":["Frame","work"],"ph":"/ˈfreɪmwɜːrk/","wt":"noun","tr":"Çerçeve","tpl":"React is a popular ___.","sent":"React is a popular <strong>framework</strong> for building user interfaces.","str":"S+V+Adj+N","rel":["Library","Django","Vue"],"why":"Framework knowledge is required in almost every dev job.","da":"Which framework should I learn first?","db":"Start with Django or Flask for Python."},
{"id":1060,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🚀","word":"Deploy","syl":["De","ploy"],"ph":"/dɪˈplɔɪ/","wt":"verb","tr":"Yayına Almak","tpl":"___ the app after testing.","sent":"<strong>Deploy</strong> the app to production after all tests pass.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Cloud","Server","CI/CD"],"why":"Deploy is a daily word for every web developer.","da":"Is the new feature ready?","db":"Yes, we can deploy it tonight."},
{"id":1061,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"📐","word":"Syntax","syl":["Syn","tax"],"ph":"/ˈsɪntæks/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sözdizimi","tpl":"A ___ error stops the program.","sent":"A <strong>syntax</strong> error stops the program from running.","str":"Adj+N+V+O","rel":["Error","Compiler","Grammar"],"why":"Syntax error is the first error every programmer sees.","da":"Why does my code not run?","db":"You have a syntax error on line 3."},
{"id":1062,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"🏛️","word":"Class","syl":["Class"],"ph":"/klɑːs/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sınıf","tpl":"Create a ___ with methods.","sent":"Create a <strong>class</strong> with all the methods you need.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Object","Method","OOP"],"why":"Class is the foundation of object-oriented programming.","da":"What is OOP?","db":"You define a class then create objects from it."},
{"id":1063,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"🧱","word":"Object","syl":["Ob","ject"],"ph":"/ˈɒbdʒɪkt/","wt":"noun","tr":"Nesne","tpl":"Create an ___ from the class.","sent":"Create an <strong>object</strong> from the class to use its methods.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Class","Instance","Method"],"why":"Object is the core unit in OOP.","da":"How many objects can I make from one class?","db":"As many as you need."},
{"id":1064,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"↩️","word":"Return","syl":["Re","turn"],"ph":"/rɪˈtɜːrn/","wt":"verb","tr":"Döndürmek","tpl":"The function will ___ a value.","sent":"The function will <strong>return</strong> a value when it finishes.","str":"S+Modal+V+O","rel":["Function","Value","Output"],"why":"Return is in every function definition.","da":"How does the function give me the result?","db":"It uses a return statement."},
{"id":1065,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"✅","word":"Boolean","syl":["Bool","e","an"],"ph":"/ˈbuːliən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Mantıksal Değer","tpl":"Return a ___ value.","sent":"Return a <strong>Boolean</strong> value — true or false.","str":"V+O [Imp]","rel":["True","False","Condition"],"why":"Boolean logic is the foundation of all programming decisions.","da":"Can I store yes or no as a value?","db":"Yes, use a Boolean — true for yes, false for no."},
{"id":1066,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"🔢","word":"Integer","syl":["In","te","ger"],"ph":"/ˈɪntɪdʒər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Tam Sayı","tpl":"Store the count as an ___.","sent":"Store the count as an <strong>integer</strong>, not a string.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Float","String","Type"],"why":"Integer is the most basic data type in programming.","da":"What type should I use for age?","db":"Use an integer — age is always a whole number."},
{"id":1067,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"⚠️","word":"Exception","syl":["Ex","cep","tion"],"ph":"/ɪkˈsepʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"İstisna / Hata","tpl":"Catch the ___ to handle errors.","sent":"Catch the <strong>exception</strong> to handle errors gracefully.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Try","Catch","Error"],"why":"Exception handling separates beginner from professional code.","da":"What happens if the user types a letter instead of a number?","db":"The program throws an exception — catch it."},
{"id":1068,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Programlama","icon":"💡","word":"Compile","syl":["Com","pile"],"ph":"/kəmˈpaɪl/","wt":"verb","tr":"Derlemek","tpl":"___ before running.","sent":"<strong>Compile</strong> the code before running it.","str":"V+O+Adv [Imp]","rel":["Compiler","Build","Error"],"why":"Compilation is required in C, Java, and many other languages.","da":"I edited the code but nothing changed.","db":"You need to compile it again."},
{"id":1069,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Veritabanı","icon":"🗄️","word":"Database","syl":["Da","ta","base"],"ph":"/ˈdeɪtəbeɪs/","wt":"noun","tr":"Veritabanı","tpl":"Connect to the ___ first.","sent":"Connect to the <strong>database</strong> before running the query.","str":"V+Prep [Imp]","rel":["SQL","Table","Query"],"why":"Database skills are required in every programming job.","da":"Where is the user data stored?","db":"In the database — we use PostgreSQL."},
{"id":1070,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Veritabanı","icon":"🔎","word":"Query","syl":["Que","ry"],"ph":"/ˈkwɪri/","wt":"noun/verb","tr":"Sorgu","tpl":"Write a ___ to find users.","sent":"Write a <strong>query</strong> to find all active users.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["SQL","SELECT","Filter"],"why":"Writing queries is the daily work of every developer.","da":"How do I get all customers?","db":"Write a SELECT query."},
{"id":1071,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Veritabanı","icon":"📋","word":"SQL","syl":["S","Q","L"],"ph":"/ˌɛskjuːˈɛl/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sorgu Dili","tpl":"Use ___ to manage data.","sent":"Use <strong>SQL</strong> to manage data in the database.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Query","SELECT","Table"],"why":"SQL is the universal database language.","da":"How do you get data from a database?","db":"With SQL queries — SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE."},
{"id":1072,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Veritabanı","icon":"📊","word":"Table","syl":["Ta","ble"],"ph":"/ˈteɪbəl/","wt":"noun","tr":"Tablo","tpl":"The users ___ has 3 columns.","sent":"The users <strong>table</strong> has columns for id, name and email.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Column","Row","Schema"],"why":"Tables are how relational databases organize data.","da":"How is the database organized?","db":"In tables — like a spreadsheet but more powerful."},
{"id":1073,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🌐","word":"Network","syl":["Net","work"],"ph":"/ˈnetwɜːrk/","wt":"noun","tr":"Ağ","tpl":"The ___ is down.","sent":"The <strong>network</strong> is down and I cannot connect.","str":"S+V+Adj","rel":["Internet","LAN","Protocol"],"why":"Network is the foundation of all IT infrastructure.","da":"I cannot access the shared drive.","db":"The network might be down."},
{"id":1074,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"📡","word":"Server","syl":["Serv","er"],"ph":"/ˈsɜːrvər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sunucu","tpl":"The ___ handles all requests.","sent":"The <strong>server</strong> handles all incoming requests.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Client","Host","Response"],"why":"Server is the most critical concept in web development.","da":"Where is the website stored?","db":"On a server — a powerful computer always online."},
{"id":1075,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"💻","word":"Client","syl":["Cli","ent"],"ph":"/ˈklaɪənt/","wt":"noun","tr":"İstemci","tpl":"The ___ sends a request.","sent":"The <strong>client</strong> sends a request and waits for a response.","str":"S+V+O+Conj","rel":["Server","Browser","App"],"why":"Client-server is the foundation of web applications.","da":"Is my browser the server or client?","db":"Your browser is the client."},
{"id":1076,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🔗","word":"Protocol","syl":["Pro","to","col"],"ph":"/ˈproʊtəkɒl/","wt":"noun","tr":"Protokol","tpl":"HTTP is a web ___.","sent":"HTTP is the standard <strong>protocol</strong> for web communication.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["HTTP","TCP","IP"],"why":"Protocol defines how devices communicate.","da":"Why does a URL start with http?","db":"That is the protocol — rules for communication."},
{"id":1077,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🌐","word":"IP Address","syl":["I","P","Ad","dress"],"ph":"/ˌaɪˈpiː ˈædrɛs/","wt":"noun","tr":"IP Adresi","tpl":"Every device has a ___.","sent":"Every device on a network has a unique <strong>IP address</strong>.","str":"S+V+Adj+N","rel":["DNS","DHCP","Router"],"why":"IP address is the postal address of every device.","da":"How does data know where to go?","db":"Every device has an IP address."},
{"id":1078,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🔒","word":"Firewall","syl":["Fire","wall"],"ph":"/ˈfaɪərwɔːl/","wt":"noun","tr":"Güvenlik Duvarı","tpl":"The ___ blocks bad traffic.","sent":"The <strong>firewall</strong> blocks all suspicious incoming traffic.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Security","Block","Network"],"why":"Firewall is the first line of network defense.","da":"How is the company network protected?","db":"We have a firewall blocking unauthorized access."},
{"id":1079,"mod":"cs","level":"A2","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🔐","word":"Encryption","syl":["En","cryp","tion"],"ph":"/ɪnˈkrɪpʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Şifreleme","tpl":"Use ___ to protect data.","sent":"Use strong <strong>encryption</strong> to protect sensitive data.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Decrypt","SSL","TLS"],"why":"Encryption is mandatory for any secure application.","da":"Can someone read my messages?","db":"Not if encryption is used."},
