{"id":1102,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Programlama","icon":"💡","word":"Semantics","syl":["Se","man","tics"],"ph":"/sɪˈmæntɪks/","wt":"noun","tr":"Anlambilim","tpl":"___ is about meaning not form.","sent":"<strong>Semantics</strong> is about the meaning and logic of code, not just its form.","str":"S+V+Prep","rel":["Syntax","Logic","Runtime"],"why":"Understanding semantics helps write correct algorithms.","da":"The code runs but gives wrong answers.","db":"That is a semantic error — the logic is wrong."},
