{"id":1104,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Programlama","icon":"🔗","word":"Inheritance","syl":["In","her","i","tance"],"ph":"/ɪnˈherɪtəns/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kalıtım","tpl":"Use ___ to reuse code.","sent":"Use <strong>inheritance</strong> to reuse code from a parent class.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Class","OOP","Polymorphism"],"why":"Inheritance is a core OOP concept in all job interviews.","da":"Why write the same code twice?","db":"Use inheritance — the child class gets everything from the parent."},
{"id":1105,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Programlama","icon":"🔄","word":"Polymorphism","syl":["Pol","y","mor","phism"],"ph":"/ˌpɒlɪˈmɔːfɪzəm/","wt":"noun","tr":"Çok Biçimlilik","tpl":"___ allows different behavior.","sent":"<strong>Polymorphism</strong> allows the same method to behave differently.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["OOP","Inheritance","Class"],"why":"Polymorphism makes code flexible and maintainable.","da":"How can one method do different things?","db":"That is polymorphism — behavior depends on the object."},
{"id":1106,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Programlama","icon":"📦","word":"Encapsulation","syl":["En","cap","su","la","tion"],"ph":"/ɪnˌkæpsjʊˈleɪʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kapsülleme","tpl":"___ hides internal details.","sent":"<strong>Encapsulation</strong> hides internal details and shows only what is needed.","str":"S+V+O+Conj","rel":["OOP","Class","Private"],"why":"Encapsulation is the third OOP pillar after inheritance.","da":"Why use private variables?","db":"That is encapsulation — hide internal details."},
{"id":1107,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔢","word":"Binary","syl":["Bi","na","ry"],"ph":"/ˈbaɪnəri/","wt":"noun/adj","tr":"İkili / Binary","tpl":"Computers store data in ___.","sent":"Computers store all data in <strong>binary</strong> — zeros and ones.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Bit","Byte","Hex"],"why":"Binary is the language of all computers.","da":"How does a computer understand anything?","db":"It uses binary — 0 and 1 for everything."},
{"id":1108,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🌳","word":"Linked List","syl":["Link","ed","List"],"ph":"/ˈlɪŋkt lɪst/","wt":"noun","tr":"Bağlı Liste","tpl":"A ___ connects nodes together.","sent":"A <strong>linked list</strong> connects nodes together in sequence.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Node","Array","Pointer"],"why":"Linked list is a classic data structure interview question.","da":"Why not just use an array?","db":"A linked list is better for frequent insertions."},
{"id":1109,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🌲","word":"Binary Tree","syl":["Bi","na","ry","Tree"],"ph":"/ˈbaɪnəri triː/","wt":"noun","tr":"İkili Ağaç","tpl":"A ___ has at most two children.","sent":"Each node in a <strong>binary tree</strong> has at most two children.","str":"S+Prep+V+Adj+N","rel":["Node","Recursion","Search"],"why":"Binary trees power many database indexes.","da":"How does fast search work in databases?","db":"Often with a binary tree structure."},
{"id":1110,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔁","word":"Iteration","syl":["It","er","a","tion"],"ph":"/ˌɪtəˈreɪʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Yineleme","tpl":"Each ___ processes one item.","sent":"Each <strong>iteration</strong> of the loop processes one item.","str":"S+Prep+V+O","rel":["Loop","Index","Array"],"why":"Iteration is the formal term for looping through data.","da":"How does the loop go through each item?","db":"One iteration at a time."},
{"id":1111,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔄","word":"CI/CD","syl":["C","I","C","D"],"ph":"/ˌsiːˈaɪˌsiːˈdiː/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sürekli Entegrasyon/Dağıtım","tpl":"___ automates deployment.","sent":"<strong>CI/CD</strong> automates building, testing and deployment.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Deploy","Pipeline","Jenkins"],"why":"CI/CD is used in every modern development team.","da":"How does code get to production automatically?","db":"Through a CI/CD pipeline."},
{"id":1112,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🧪","word":"Testing","syl":["Test","ing"],"ph":"/ˈtɛstɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Test Etme","tpl":"___ catches bugs early.","sent":"<strong>Testing</strong> catches bugs before users find them.","str":"S+V+O+Adv","rel":["Unit Test","Debug","QA"],"why":"Testing is a required skill in every software job.","da":"How do you make sure code works?","db":"By writing tests for every function."},
{"id":1113,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🏗️","word":"Architecture","syl":["Ar","chi","tec","ture"],"ph":"/ˈɑːrkɪtektʃər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Mimari","tpl":"Design the ___ before coding.","sent":"Design the <strong>architecture</strong> before writing any code.","str":"V+O+Adv [Imp]","rel":["System Design","Pattern","Microservice"],"why":"Architecture decisions determine the success of a project.","da":"How do you plan a large system?","db":"Start with the architecture — design before coding."},
{"id":1114,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🔄","word":"TCP/IP","syl":["T","C","P","I","P"],"ph":"/ˌtiːsiːpiːˌaɪˈpiː/","wt":"noun","tr":"İletim Kontrol Protokolü","tpl":"___ is the base of the internet.","sent":"<strong>TCP/IP</strong> is the foundational protocol of the internet.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Protocol","Packet","Network"],"why":"TCP/IP powers all internet communication.","da":"How does data travel across the internet?","db":"Using TCP/IP — the base protocol."},
{"id":1115,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🔒","word":"HTTPS","syl":["H","T","T","P","S"],"ph":"/ˌeɪtʃtiːtiːpiːˈɛs/","wt":"noun","tr":"Güvenli HTTP","tpl":"Use ___ for secure connections.","sent":"Use <strong>HTTPS</strong> to secure data between browser and server.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["HTTP","SSL","TLS"],"why":"HTTPS is required for all modern websites.","da":"Is it safe to enter my password here?","db":"Check if the URL starts with HTTPS."},
{"id":1116,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"☁️","word":"VPN","syl":["V","P","N"],"ph":"/ˌviːpiːˈɛn/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sanal Özel Ağ","tpl":"Use a ___ to browse securely.","sent":"Use a <strong>VPN</strong> to browse securely and hide your IP.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Encryption","Privacy","IP"],"why":"VPN is essential for remote work security.","da":"I need to access the office server from home.","db":"Connect through the VPN first."},
{"id":1117,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🔄","word":"DHCP","syl":["D","H","C","P"],"ph":"/ˌdiːeɪtʃsiːˈpiː/","wt":"noun","tr":"Dinamik IP Yapılandırma","tpl":"___ assigns IP addresses automatically.","sent":"<strong>DHCP</strong> automatically assigns IP addresses to devices.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["IP","Router","Static IP"],"why":"DHCP is what makes joining WiFi automatic.","da":"Do I need to type an IP manually?","db":"No, DHCP handles that automatically."},
{"id":1118,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔁","word":"Refactoring","syl":["Re","fac","tor","ing"],"ph":"/ˌriːˈfæktərɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Yeniden Düzenleme","tpl":"___ improves code quality.","sent":"<strong>Refactoring</strong> improves code quality without changing its behavior.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Clean Code","Debug","Optimize"],"why":"Refactoring is a critical skill for maintainable software.","da":"The code works but is very messy.","db":"You need to do some refactoring."},
{"id":1119,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📦","word":"Package","syl":["Pack","age"],"ph":"/ˈpækɪdʒ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Paket","tpl":"Install the ___ with pip.","sent":"Install the <strong>package</strong> with pip to add new functionality.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Library","npm","Import"],"why":"Package management is essential for any project.","da":"How do I add this feature?","db":"Install the package and import it."},
{"id":1120,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veritabanı","icon":"🔗","word":"Join","syl":["Join"],"ph":"/dʒɔɪn/","wt":"verb/noun","tr":"Birleştirme","tpl":"Use ___ to combine tables.","sent":"Use <strong>JOIN</strong> to combine data from two tables.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["SQL","Table","Relation"],"why":"JOIN is the most powerful SQL operation.","da":"I need data from two tables at once.","db":"Use a JOIN query."},
{"id":1121,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veritabanı","icon":"📐","word":"Schema","syl":["Sche","ma"],"ph":"/ˈskiːmə/","wt":"noun","tr":"Şema","tpl":"Design the ___ first.","sent":"Design the database <strong>schema</strong> before writing any code.","str":"V+O+Adv [Imp]","rel":["Table","Model","Migration"],"why":"Schema design is the most important database decision.","da":"What tables do we need?","db":"Let us design the schema first."},
{"id":1122,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veri","icon":"📊","word":"Hash Table","syl":["Hash","Ta","ble"],"ph":"/hæʃ ˈteɪbəl/","wt":"noun","tr":"Hash Tablosu","tpl":"A ___ provides O(1) lookup.","sent":"A <strong>hash table</strong> provides very fast O(1) average lookup time.","str":"S+V+Adj+N","rel":["Dictionary","Key","Value"],"why":"Hash tables power Python dictionaries and database indexes.","da":"How do dictionaries work so fast?","db":"They use a hash table underneath."},
{"id":1123,"mod":"cs","level":"B1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔄","word":"Queue","syl":["Queue"],"ph":"/kjuː/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kuyruk","tpl":"A ___ is first in first out.","sent":"A <strong>queue</strong> is FIFO — first in, first out.","str":"S+V+Definition","rel":["Stack","FIFO","Buffer"],"why":"Queues are used in operating systems and message systems.","da":"How do print jobs wait their turn?","db":"They are stored in a queue."},
