{"id":1171,"mod":"cs","level":"B2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔀","word":"Race Condition","syl":["Race","Con","di","tion"],"ph":"/reɪs kənˈdɪʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Yarış Durumu","tpl":"A ___ causes unpredictable behavior.","sent":"A <strong>race condition</strong> occurs when two threads access the same data simultaneously.","str":"S+V+Adv [Definition]","rel":["Thread","Mutex","Concurrency"],"why":"Race conditions cause the most mysterious bugs in concurrent code.","da":"The bug appears randomly.","db":"Might be a race condition — check shared data access."},
