{"id":1197,"mod":"cs","level":"B2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📊","word":"Observability","syl":["Ob","serv","a","bil","i","ty"],"ph":"/əbˌzɜːrvəˈbɪlɪti/","wt":"noun","tr":"Gözlemlenebilirlik","tpl":"___ shows what is happening inside.","sent":"Good <strong>observability</strong> lets you understand what is happening inside the system.","str":"Adj+S+V+O","rel":["Monitoring","Logging","Tracing"],"why":"Observability is critical for debugging production issues.","da":"Something went wrong in production but we do not know where.","db":"You need better observability — add logging and tracing."},
{"id":1198,"mod":"cs","level":"B2","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔄","word":"ETL","syl":["E","T","L"],"ph":"/ˌiːtiːˈɛl/","wt":"noun","tr":"Çıkar Dönüştür Yükle","tpl":"___ moves data between systems.","sent":"<strong>ETL</strong> extracts data, transforms it, and loads it into the warehouse.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Data Pipeline","Warehouse","Spark"],"why":"ETL is the foundation of every data engineering project.","da":"How does data get from the app to the analytics system?","db":"Through an ETL pipeline."},
{"id":1199,"mod":"cs","level":"B2","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📦","word":"Immutable Infrastructure","syl":["Im","mu","ta","ble","In","fra","struc","ture"],"ph":"/ɪˈmjuːtəbəl ˈɪnfrəstrʌktʃər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Değiştirilemez Altyapı","tpl":"___ replaces rather than updates.","sent":"<strong>Immutable infrastructure</strong> means replacing servers rather than updating them.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Docker","DevOps","Deploy"],"why":"Immutable infrastructure eliminates configuration drift.","da":"Why do we build new servers instead of updating existing ones?","db":"Immutable infrastructure — replace, never modify."},
{"id":1200,"mod":"cs","level":"B2","cat":"Güvenlik","icon":"🔐","word":"Zero-Day Exploit","syl":["Ze","ro","Day","Ex","ploit"],"ph":"/ˈzɪərəʊ deɪ ˈɛksplɔɪt/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sıfır Gün İstismarı","tpl":"A ___ uses unknown vulnerabilities.","sent":"A <strong>zero-day exploit</strong> attacks a vulnerability before a fix exists.","str":"S+V+O+Adv","rel":["Vulnerability","Patch","Security"],"why":"Zero-day exploits are the most dangerous security threats.","da":"How can a system be attacked if it is fully patched?","db":"Through a zero-day exploit — an unknown vulnerability."},

