{"id":1201,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🧮","word":"CAP Theorem","syl":["C","A","P","The","o","rem"],"ph":"/kæp ˈθɪərəm/","wt":"noun","tr":"CAP Teoremi","tpl":"___ defines distributed system trade-offs.","sent":"The <strong>CAP theorem</strong> says a distributed system can only guarantee two of three: consistency, availability, partition tolerance.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Distributed System","Consistency","NoSQL"],"why":"CAP theorem guides every distributed database design decision.","da":"Why can we not have both consistency and availability?","db":"Because of the CAP theorem."},
{"id":1202,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔄","word":"Event Sourcing","syl":["E","vent","Sourc","ing"],"ph":"/ɪˈvɛnt ˈsɔːrsɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Olay Kaynağı","tpl":"___ stores state as events.","sent":"<strong>Event sourcing</strong> stores the full history of state changes as a sequence of events.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["CQRS","Event Driven","Kafka"],"why":"Event sourcing enables full audit trails and time-travel debugging.","da":"How can we see every change ever made?","db":"Use event sourcing — every change is an event."},
{"id":1203,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔀","word":"CQRS","syl":["C","Q","R","S"],"ph":"/ˈsiːkjuːɑːrˈɛs/","wt":"noun","tr":"Komut Sorgu Ayrımı","tpl":"___ separates reads from writes.","sent":"<strong>CQRS</strong> separates the read model from the write model for better scalability.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["Event Sourcing","Architecture","Microservice"],"why":"CQRS improves performance in high-read-write systems.","da":"The read and write loads are very different.","db":"Use CQRS — separate models for reads and writes."},
{"id":1204,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🧠","word":"Reinforcement Learning","syl":["Re","in","force","ment","Learn","ing"],"ph":"/ˌriːɪnˈfɔːrsmənt ˈlɜːrnɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Pekiştirmeli Öğrenme","tpl":"___ learns through reward signals.","sent":"<strong>Reinforcement learning</strong> trains agents through trial and error with reward signals.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["AI","Neural Network","Policy"],"why":"RL powers AlphaGo, game AI, and robotics.","da":"How does the AI learn to play chess?","db":"Through reinforcement learning — reward for winning moves."},
{"id":1205,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔮","word":"Transformer Architecture","syl":["Trans","form","er","Ar","chi","tec","ture"],"ph":"/trænsˈfɔːrmər ˈɑːrkɪtektʃər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Transformer Mimarisi","tpl":"GPT uses the ___.","sent":"GPT uses the <strong>transformer architecture</strong> with self-attention mechanisms.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Attention","Neural Network","LLM"],"why":"Transformer architecture powers ChatGPT and all modern LLMs.","da":"What makes ChatGPT different from older AI?","db":"The transformer architecture and self-attention."},
{"id":1206,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📊","word":"Domain Driven Design","syl":["Do","main","Driv","en","De","sign"],"ph":"/dəˈmeɪn ˈdrɪvən dɪˈzaɪn/","wt":"noun","tr":"Alan Güdümlü Tasarım","tpl":"Use ___ for complex domains.","sent":"Use <strong>domain-driven design</strong> to model complex business logic clearly.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Architecture","Bounded Context","Microservice"],"why":"DDD is the standard approach for designing enterprise systems.","da":"How do you model very complex business rules?","db":"With domain-driven design."},
{"id":1207,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔬","word":"Hyperparameter Tuning","syl":["Hy","per","pa","ram","e","ter","Tun","ing"],"ph":"/ˈhaɪpərˌpærəmɪtər ˈtjuːnɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Hiperparametre Ayarı","tpl":"___ optimizes model performance.","sent":"<strong>Hyperparameter tuning</strong> optimizes settings to maximize model accuracy.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["ML","Cross-Validation","Grid Search"],"why":"Hyperparameter tuning is a key ML engineering skill.","da":"The model accuracy is 75% — can we do better?","db":"Try hyperparameter tuning — adjust learning rate and depth."},
{"id":1208,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🌐","word":"Consensus Algorithm","syl":["Con","sen","sus","Al","go","rithm"],"ph":"/kənˈsɛnsəs ˈælɡərɪðəm/","wt":"noun","tr":"Mutabakat Algoritması","tpl":"Raft is a ___ for distributed systems.","sent":"Raft is a <strong>consensus algorithm</strong> used to agree on state in distributed systems.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Distributed System","Raft","Paxos"],"why":"Consensus algorithms are fundamental to blockchain and distributed DBs.","da":"How do multiple servers agree on the same state?","db":"Through a consensus algorithm like Raft or Paxos."},
{"id":1209,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔐","word":"Cryptographic Hash","syl":["Cryp","to","graph","ic","Hash"],"ph":"/ˌkrɪptəˈɡræfɪk hæʃ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kriptografik Hash","tpl":"SHA-256 is a ___ function.","sent":"SHA-256 is a <strong>cryptographic hash</strong> function that is practically irreversible.","str":"S+V+Adj+N","rel":["SHA-256","Security","Blockchain"],"why":"Cryptographic hashing secures passwords and blockchain transactions.","da":"How are passwords stored safely?","db":"As cryptographic hashes — never in plain text."},
{"id":1210,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🌐","word":"Serverless","syl":["Serv","er","less"],"ph":"/ˈsɜːvərləs/","wt":"adj/noun","tr":"Sunucusuz","tpl":"Use ___ to reduce infrastructure costs.","sent":"Use <strong>serverless</strong> functions to run code without managing servers.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Lambda","Cloud","FaaS"],"why":"Serverless reduces cost and complexity for event-driven workloads.","da":"We are paying a lot for idle servers.","db":"Switch to serverless — pay only for execution time."},
{"id":1211,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"📊","word":"Embedding","syl":["Em","bed","ding"],"ph":"/ɪmˈbɛdɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Gömme / Embedding","tpl":"___ converts text to vectors.","sent":"<strong>Embedding</strong> converts text into numerical vectors for machine learning.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["NLP","Vector","Transformer"],"why":"Embeddings are the foundation of all modern NLP systems.","da":"How does AI understand the meaning of words?","db":"Through embeddings — words become vectors in space."},
{"id":1212,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔄","word":"Eventual Consistency","syl":["E","ven","tu","al","Con","sis","ten","cy"],"ph":"/ɪˈventʃuəl kənˈsɪstənsi/","wt":"noun","tr":"Nihai Tutarlılık","tpl":"NoSQL databases use ___.","sent":"Many NoSQL databases use <strong>eventual consistency</strong> — all nodes will agree eventually.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["CAP Theorem","NoSQL","Distributed"],"why":"Eventual consistency is the trade-off most distributed databases make.","da":"Why do I see different data on different servers?","db":"Eventual consistency — they will sync soon."},
{"id":1213,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"⚡","word":"SIMD","syl":["S","I","M","D"],"ph":"/ˌɛsaɪɛmˈdiː/","wt":"noun","tr":"Tek Komut Çok Veri","tpl":"___ speeds up parallel computations.","sent":"<strong>SIMD</strong> executes the same instruction on multiple data points simultaneously.","str":"S+V+O+Adv","rel":["GPU","Vectorization","Performance"],"why":"SIMD is critical for image processing and scientific computing.","da":"How do CPUs process image data so fast?","db":"With SIMD — process many pixels at once."},
{"id":1214,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"⛓️","word":"Blockchain","syl":["Block","chain"],"ph":"/ˈblɒktʃeɪn/","wt":"noun","tr":"Blokzincir","tpl":"___ is an immutable ledger.","sent":"A <strong>blockchain</strong> is a distributed, immutable ledger secured by cryptography.","str":"S+V+N","rel":["Cryptography","Consensus","Distributed"],"why":"Blockchain underpins Bitcoin and many enterprise systems.","da":"How is the Bitcoin transaction history tamper-proof?","db":"Through blockchain — changing one block breaks the entire chain."},
{"id":1215,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔄","word":"Saga Pattern","syl":["Sa","ga","Pat","tern"],"ph":"/ˈsɑːɡə ˈpætərn/","wt":"noun","tr":"Saga Deseni","tpl":"___ manages distributed transactions.","sent":"The <strong>saga pattern</strong> manages long-running distributed transactions with compensating actions.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["Microservice","CQRS","Transaction"],"why":"Saga pattern solves distributed transaction problems in microservices.","da":"How do you handle transactions across multiple services?","db":"Use the saga pattern with compensating transactions."},
{"id":1216,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🧠","word":"Attention Mechanism","syl":["At","ten","tion","Mech","a","nism"],"ph":"/əˈtɛnʃən ˈmɛkənɪzəm/","wt":"noun","tr":"Dikkat Mekanizması","tpl":"___ focuses on relevant parts.","sent":"The <strong>attention mechanism</strong> allows models to focus on the most relevant parts of input.","str":"S+V+O+Inf","rel":["Transformer","NLP","Neural Network"],"why":"Attention mechanism is the breakthrough behind modern AI.","da":"How does the AI know which words are important?","db":"Through the attention mechanism."},
{"id":1217,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📊","word":"Circuit Breaker","syl":["Cir","cuit","Break","er"],"ph":"/ˈsɜːkɪt ˈbreɪkər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Devre Kesici","tpl":"A ___ prevents cascade failures.","sent":"A <strong>circuit breaker</strong> stops a failing service from causing cascade failures.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Microservice","Resilience","Hystrix"],"why":"Circuit breakers are essential for resilient microservice architectures.","da":"One service failing is bringing down the whole system.","db":"Add a circuit breaker to isolate the failure."},
{"id":1218,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"📈","word":"A/B Testing","syl":["A","B","Test","ing"],"ph":"/ˌeɪˈbiː ˈtɛstɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"A/B Testi","tpl":"Use ___ to compare versions.","sent":"Use <strong>A/B testing</strong> to compare two versions and pick the better one.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Analytics","Experiment","Statistics"],"why":"A/B testing is the scientific method of product decisions.","da":"Which button color converts better?","db":"Run an A/B test — half see blue, half see green."},
{"id":1219,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Güvenlik","icon":"🔐","word":"Homomorphic Encryption","syl":["Ho","mo","mor","phic","En","cryp","tion"],"ph":"/ˌhɒməˈmɔːfɪk ɪnˈkrɪpʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Homomorfik Şifreleme","tpl":"___ enables computation on encrypted data.","sent":"<strong>Homomorphic encryption</strong> allows computations on encrypted data without decrypting it.","str":"S+V+O+Ger","rel":["Privacy","Cloud","Cryptography"],"why":"Homomorphic encryption enables privacy-preserving cloud computing.","da":"Can we compute on sensitive data without seeing it?","db":"Yes, with homomorphic encryption."},
{"id":1220,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🏗️","word":"Hexagonal Architecture","syl":["Hex","ag","o","nal","Ar","chi","tec","ture"],"ph":"/hɛkˈsæɡənəl ˈɑːrkɪtektʃər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Altıgen Mimari","tpl":"___ isolates business logic.","sent":"<strong>Hexagonal architecture</strong> isolates core business logic from external systems.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["Clean Architecture","Ports","Adapters"],"why":"Hexagonal architecture makes systems testable and maintainable.","da":"How do we make the core logic independent of the database?","db":"Use hexagonal architecture — business logic in the center."},
{"id":1221,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🧠","word":"Federated Learning","syl":["Fed","er","at","ed","Learn","ing"],"ph":"/ˈfɛdəreɪtɪd ˈlɜːrnɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Federe Öğrenme","tpl":"___ trains without sharing raw data.","sent":"<strong>Federated learning</strong> trains ML models across devices without sharing raw data.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["Privacy","ML","Distributed"],"why":"Federated learning enables AI on private data.","da":"How does Google train models without accessing my data?","db":"Through federated learning — the model comes to the data."},
{"id":1222,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔄","word":"Idempotency","syl":["I","dem","po","ten","cy"],"ph":"/aɪˈdɛmpətənsi/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kuvvetlilik","tpl":"API endpoints should be ___.","sent":"API endpoints should be <strong>idempotent</strong> — calling them twice has the same effect as once.","str":"S+V+Adj","rel":["REST","API","Retry"],"why":"Idempotency prevents duplicate processing in distributed systems.","da":"What if the request is sent twice due to retry?","db":"Design for idempotency — same result every time."},
{"id":1223,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"📊","word":"Knowledge Graph","syl":["Knowl","edge","Graph"],"ph":"/ˈnɒlɪdʒ ɡrɑːf/","wt":"noun","tr":"Bilgi Grafiği","tpl":"Google uses a ___ for search.","sent":"Google uses a <strong>knowledge graph</strong> to link concepts and improve search results.","str":"S+V+O+Inf","rel":["Graph Database","NLP","AI"],"why":"Knowledge graphs power semantic search and AI reasoning.","da":"How does Google understand that Paris is in France?","db":"Through its knowledge graph."},
{"id":1224,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔀","word":"Backpressure","syl":["Back","pres","sure"],"ph":"/ˈbækˌprɛʃər/","wt":"noun","tr":"Geri Basınç","tpl":"___ prevents system overload.","sent":"<strong>Backpressure</strong> signals upstream services to slow down when the system is overwhelmed.","str":"S+V+O+Adv","rel":["Queue","Reactive","Stream"],"why":"Backpressure is essential in reactive and streaming systems.","da":"The queue keeps growing and the system is crashing.","db":"Implement backpressure — tell producers to slow down."},
{"id":1225,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔮","word":"Causal Inference","syl":["Caus","al","In","fer","ence"],"ph":"/ˈkɔːzəl ˈɪnfərəns/","wt":"noun","tr":"Nedensellik Çıkarımı","tpl":"___ finds cause and effect.","sent":"<strong>Causal inference</strong> identifies cause-and-effect relationships rather than just correlations.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["Statistics","ML","Experiment"],"why":"Causal inference distinguishes correlation from causation in data.","da":"How do we know if the marketing campaign actually worked?","db":"Through causal inference — control for confounders."},
{"id":1226,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"📊","word":"Chaos Engineering","syl":["Cha","os","En","gi","neer","ing"],"ph":"/ˈkeɪɒs ˌɛndʒɪˈnɪərɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Kaos Mühendisliği","tpl":"Netflix uses ___ to test resilience.","sent":"Netflix uses <strong>chaos engineering</strong> to deliberately break things and find weaknesses.","str":"S+V+O+Inf","rel":["Resilience","Microservice","Testing"],"why":"Chaos engineering finds weaknesses before they cause outages.","da":"How does Netflix ensure reliability?","db":"By practicing chaos engineering — breaking things on purpose."},
{"id":1227,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🧮","word":"Gradient Descent","syl":["Gra","di","ent","De","scent"],"ph":"/ˈɡreɪdiənt dɪˈsɛnt/","wt":"noun","tr":"Gradyan İnişi","tpl":"___ optimizes neural network weights.","sent":"<strong>Gradient descent</strong> iteratively adjusts weights to minimize the loss function.","str":"S+V+O+Inf","rel":["Backpropagation","Neural Network","Loss Function"],"why":"Gradient descent is how every neural network learns.","da":"How does the model improve with more data?","db":"Through gradient descent — small weight adjustments each step."},
{"id":1228,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Güvenlik","icon":"🔐","word":"Side-Channel Attack","syl":["Side","Chan","nel","At","tack"],"ph":"/saɪd ˈtʃænəl əˈtæk/","wt":"noun","tr":"Yan Kanal Saldırısı","tpl":"A ___ exploits physical leakage.","sent":"A <strong>side-channel attack</strong> extracts information from physical signals like power or timing.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["Security","Hardware","Cryptography"],"why":"Side-channel attacks bypass mathematical security entirely.","da":"How can a cryptographic system be broken without cracking the math?","db":"Through a side-channel attack on the physical implementation."},
{"id":1229,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"⚡","word":"Reactive Programming","syl":["Re","ac","tive","Pro","gram","ming"],"ph":"/riˈæktɪv ˈproʊɡræmɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Reaktif Programlama","tpl":"___ handles streams of events.","sent":"<strong>Reactive programming</strong> handles asynchronous streams of data elegantly.","str":"S+V+O+Adv","rel":["RxJS","Observable","Async"],"why":"Reactive programming is the paradigm for modern UI and streaming.","da":"How does the UI react to every user action instantly?","db":"Through reactive programming — subscribe to event streams."},
{"id":1230,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🧠","word":"Self-Supervised Learning","syl":["Self","Su","per","vised","Learn","ing"],"ph":"/sɛlf ˈsuːpərvaɪzd ˈlɜːrnɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Öz Denetimli Öğrenme","tpl":"GPT uses ___ on text data.","sent":"GPT uses <strong>self-supervised learning</strong> to predict the next word from billions of examples.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["LLM","Transformer","Pre-training"],"why":"Self-supervised learning enabled the LLM revolution.","da":"How was GPT trained with no labeled data?","db":"Through self-supervised learning — predicting masked tokens."},
{"id":1231,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔀","word":"Dead Letter Queue","syl":["Dead","Let","ter","Queue"],"ph":"/dɛd ˈlɛtər kjuː/","wt":"noun","tr":"Ölü Mektup Kuyruğu","tpl":"Send failed messages to ___.","sent":"Send failed messages to the <strong>dead letter queue</strong> for manual review.","str":"V+O+Prep [Imp]","rel":["Message Queue","Kafka","Error Handling"],"why":"DLQ prevents message loss in distributed systems.","da":"What happens to messages that fail to process?","db":"They go to the dead letter queue for inspection."},
{"id":1232,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"📊","word":"Overfitting","syl":["O","ver","fit","ting"],"ph":"/ˈoʊvərˌfɪtɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Aşırı Uydurma","tpl":"___ hurts model generalization.","sent":"<strong>Overfitting</strong> occurs when the model memorizes training data and fails on new data.","str":"S+V+Adv","rel":["Regularization","Dropout","Cross-Validation"],"why":"Overfitting is the most common ML model failure.","da":"The model scores 99% on training but 60% on test data.","db":"Classic overfitting — add regularization or dropout."},
{"id":1233,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🏗️","word":"Strangler Fig Pattern","syl":["Stran","gler","Fig","Pat","tern"],"ph":"/ˈstræŋɡlər fɪɡ ˈpætərn/","wt":"noun","tr":"Sarmaşık Deseni","tpl":"Use ___ to migrate from monolith.","sent":"Use the <strong>strangler fig pattern</strong> to gradually migrate a monolith to microservices.","str":"V+O+Inf [Imp]","rel":["Migration","Monolith","Microservice"],"why":"Strangler fig is the safest way to migrate legacy systems.","da":"How do we move away from the old monolith?","db":"Use the strangler fig pattern — replace pieces gradually."},
{"id":1234,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"📡","word":"QUIC Protocol","syl":["Q","U","I","C","Pro","to","col"],"ph":"/kwɪk ˈproʊtəkɒl/","wt":"noun","tr":"QUIC Protokolü","tpl":"HTTP/3 uses the ___.","sent":"HTTP/3 uses the <strong>QUIC protocol</strong> for faster, more reliable connections.","str":"S+V+O","rel":["HTTP/3","UDP","Performance"],"why":"QUIC is the future of internet transport — used by Google.","da":"Why is HTTP/3 faster than HTTP/2?","db":"Because QUIC eliminates head-of-line blocking."},
{"id":1235,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Veri","icon":"🔮","word":"Regularization","syl":["Reg","u","lar","i","za","tion"],"ph":"/ˌreɡjʊlərɪˈzeɪʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Düzenlileştirme","tpl":"L2 ___ reduces overfitting.","sent":"L2 <strong>regularization</strong> penalizes large weights to prevent overfitting.","str":"S+V+O+Inf","rel":["Overfitting","L1","Dropout"],"why":"Regularization is essential for training generalizable ML models.","da":"How do we prevent the model from memorizing the data?","db":"Apply regularization — L1, L2, or dropout."},
{"id":1236,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Yazılım","icon":"🔄","word":"Backpropagation","syl":["Back","prop","a","ga","tion"],"ph":"/ˌbækˌprɒpəˈɡeɪʃən/","wt":"noun","tr":"Geri Yayılım","tpl":"___ computes gradients in neural networks.","sent":"<strong>Backpropagation</strong> computes gradients layer by layer to update weights.","str":"S+V+O+Adv","rel":["Gradient Descent","Neural Network","Loss"],"why":"Backpropagation is the algorithm that made deep learning possible.","da":"How does the neural network know which weights to update?","db":"Through backpropagation — errors flow backward."},
{"id":1237,"mod":"cs","level":"C1","cat":"Ağ","icon":"🌐","word":"Software Defined Networking","syl":["Soft","ware","De","fined","Net","work","ing"],"ph":"/ˈsɒftweər dɪˈfaɪnd ˈnetwɜːrkɪŋ/","wt":"noun","tr":"Yazılım Tanımlı Ağ","tpl":"___ separates control from data.","sent":"<strong>Software-defined networking</strong> separates the control plane from the data plane.","str":"S+V+O+Prep","rel":["Network","Virtualization","Cloud"],"why":"SDN enables programmable networks for cloud computing.","da":"How do cloud providers manage huge networks?","db":"Through software-defined networking."},
